 only when MACD crosses above MACDs (bullish crossover) or exits when it crosses below. |  ---  ### Key Takeaways for Traders  1. **Trend Confirmation**      - SPY is firmly in an uptrend: price > 50‑SMA, positive MACD, and well above the 200‑SMA.      - Use the 50‑SMA as a dynamic support; consider buying on pullbacks to it.  2. **Momentum & Volatility**      - Positive MACD and moderate ATR (~10) indicate momentum is strong but volatility is controlled.      - Avoid entering during sharp swings that exceed 1‑ATR, which could widen your stop loss dramatically.  3. **Overbought Signals**      - RSI approaching 70 suggests a potential short-term pullback.      - Combine RSI signals with MACD crossovers or VWMA divergences before taking bearish positions.  4. **Risk Management**      - Set stop‑losses around 1‑ATR below entry to cap risk at ~2% of the trade size.      - Use Bollinger Middle as a quick reference for dynamic support/resistance in fast markets.  5. **Entry/Exit Strategy (Sample)**    | Action | Trigger | Confirmation | Stop / Target | |--------|---------|--------------|---------------| | Long | Price pulls to 50‑SMA + MACD crosses above signal | VWMA > price, RSI < 70 | Stop 1 ATR below entry; target 2 ATR or next swing high (~660) | | Short | RSI > 75 & MACD crosses below signal | VWMA < price | Stop 1 ATR above entry; target 2 ATR or swing low (~630) |  ---  #### Markdown Summary Table  ```markdown | Indicator      | Trend (last 30d)       | Key Insight                          | Suggested Action                    | |----------------|------------------------|--------------------------------------|-------------------------------------| | close_50_sma   | Rising, above price    | Medium‑term bullish support          | Long on pullback to SMA              | | macd           | Positive, rising       | Momentum backing trend               | Confirm long/short entries           | | rsi            | 65‑70 (near overbought)| Possible short‑term pullback      